No fewer than 13 people were reportedly killed in a multiple car accident at Tashan Maiturare and Takandan Giwa, all at Jos road in Toro local government area of Bauchi State. The accidents which occurred at about  9pm on Thursday involved a Peugeot J5 bus with another car in a head on collision, which immediately bust into flames and consumed the lives of 11 passengers. The second accident occurred in the early hours of Friday involving a Vectra saloon car at Takandan Giwa where the car veered off the road, leading to the death of two passengers. Sources told LEADERSHIP that the two accidents were caused by violation of traffic rules by the drivers of the vehicles. The Bauchi Sector Command of the Federal Road Safety Corp (FRSC) who confirmed the development said they were still gathering details and will revert. But was yet to do so as at the time of filing this report.  